sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pSC101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was amplified from pSB4A3-P1010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pSC101 origin of replication which is supposed to have low copy number. This was the origin used in Michael Elowitz's repressilator and in Bujard's pZS4Int-1 vector with mutations introduced to eliminate a SpeI site. It is also the origin of replication in pSB4* series plasmids.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The replication origin boundaries were chosen quite liberally (i.e. they might include more sequence than is strictly necessary) because a different version of this origin (BBa_I50040) was shown to be non-functional.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
